This project presents a practical approach to improving retail inventory accuracy using data-driven forecasting. By combining statistical models, modern machine-learning techniques, and reinforcement learning, the study builds a structured framework capable of predicting demand, planning reorder cycles, and reducing supply-chain inefficiencies.

CoPhyML is a coordinated physics-integrated machine learning framework designed for reliable modeling of complex engineering systems under limited and noise-contaminated data. The framework consists of three components: a knowledge-driven module, a data-driven module, and an integration layer.
A curated list of awesome Machine Learning frameworks, libraries and software. With repository stars and forks
A machine learning project built with Swift and Apples Natural Language framework to perform real-time sentiment analysis on user input.
Predict traffic accident severity using advanced machine learning and explainable AI, enhancing road safety with clear insights from comprehensive data analysis.

This repository provides a machine learning framework that integrates structural and coevolutionary features to classify mutations as compensatory, offering insights into evolutionary adaptation and protein stability
A machine learning framework analyzing 80k+ support interactions to predict customer satisfaction (CSAT) and optimize agent allocation.

Neuralisp is a modular machine learning framework for Common Lisp, focused on deep learning models. It offers a high-performance tensor library, various neural network layers, activation functions, optimizers, and loss functions. Designed for rapid model creation, training, and testing across diverse tasks.
an open-sourced highly automated machine learning Python framework for data-driven geochemistry discovery

This project implements the Double Machine Learning (DML) framework to estimate heterogeneous treatment effects using high-dimensional data. It includes synthetic data generation, cross-fitting, residualization, nuisance modeling with ML algorithms, and final ATE estimation with detailedevaluation.
This project implements a scale-guided multi-organ segmentation framework using statistical machine learning and a ResNet-based deep learning model.

Portfolio of 8 machine learning projects completed through the UT Austin x Great Learning 7-month postgraduate program. Demonstrates proficiency in Python, ML algorithms, ANN, CNN, NLP and AI development frameworks.

LEO CDP is an open-source, AI-first Customer Data Platform for building customizable, self-hosted, privacy-friendly CDP infrastructure. It unifies data collection, enables real-time analytics, audience segmentation, and personalized marketing  powered by big data and machine learning.
Interpretable Machine Learning Framework for Designing High Ionic Conductivity in Low-Temperature Lithium-Ion Battery Electrolytes

In this study, we introduce a novel machine learning based framework that predicts austenitic grain growth behaviour directly from chemical composition and process conditions, utilizing a comprehensive dataset of 1039 experimentally validated samples. Among various algorithms tested, the XGBoost model demonstrated exceptional predictive capability
The AIP-G 1.0 (Alzheimers disease, Inhibitor Predictor for GSK-3, version 1.0) pipeline implements a two-stage machine learning framework for predicting GSK-3 inhibitors for Alzheimers disease.

This project builds a machine-learningdriven decision engine that detects fraudulent financial transactions and quantifies its business impact. It forms the foundation of a scalable risk intelligence framework.

This project proposes a predictive data-driven framework to forecast restaurant health inspection scores and identify establishments at higher risk of violations using machine learning models using the San Francisco Health Inspection Scores (2024-current) dataset as a baseline
A Physics-Informed Machine Learning (PIML) framework for detecting topological anomalies in embedded systems

This repository contains the implementation of a hybrid physics-machine learning framework for autonomous pH adjustment in complex buffered systems. The system combines Theoretical Titration Curve Generation modeling with active learning to enable rapid, precise pH optimization using low-cost automated hardware.

This project presents an AI-Driven IoT Framework designed to automate the process of fruit detection, ripeness classification, and autonomous plucking in modern smart farms. By integrating computer vision, machine learning, robotic control, and IoT connectivity, the system aims to improve harvesting efficiency, reduce labor dependency.
Machine Learning and NLP-Based Resume Parsing Framework & Generator
A machine learning project using the FastAI deeplearning framework and timm library. The model used was efficientnet_b0, trained on real-world healthy and diseased tomato leaf images.

A fully manual neural network implementation developed for my university project. This project includes weight initialization, forward propagation, backpropagation, sigmoid activation, gradient computation, and parameter updates implemented from scratch without using machine learning frameworks.
An open-source machine learning framework for global analyses of parton distributions.

A full-stack AI-powered stock market prediction platform built using Django REST Framework (DRF) for the backend and React.js for the frontend. This project leverages machine learning models to analyze historical stock data and predict future trends, helping users make data-driven investment decisions.
Machine Learning Pipeline Frameworks to Predict Directional Anisotropic Permeabilities From Porous Media Image

Genex is a full-stack application designed to assist doctors in predicting autoimmune diseases and managing personalized treatment plans. The system uses machine learning on patient gene expression data and integrates a digital twin framework to simulate drug-gene and drug-drug interactions, helping clinicians make informed therapeutic decisions.
Anvil is a Rust-based machine learning framework designed to combine the performance of low-level linear algebra with the ease of high-level ML APIs.

A web application that predicts disease likelihood from patient input using a machine learning model and exposes the model via a Django web app (REST API + web UI).   Built with Python, scikit-learn, pandas (model), and Django + Django REST Framework (backend & API). Ideal as a small end-to-end demo for healthcare/ML portfolios.

Stroke Prediction with Explainable AI: A robust machine learning framework for predicting stroke risk using classical models, focusing on handling class imbalance and providing clinical interpretability with SHAP.

All projects are built and executed using Google Colab, leveraging real-world datasets, modern frameworks, and best practices in model development and deployment.

A platform developed from an open framework to help AI researchers and developers to rapidly prototype, test and deploy workflows that include machine learning models as worker components. The workflow can be invoked on command line or web service, as well as integrated into UX/UI as part of a larger intelligent solution.

This repository contains an experimental trading-bot framework built around machine learning, computer vision and stochastic modelling, with the goal of helping evaluate stocks (undervalued / fairly valued / overvalued) and ultimately support automated trading decisions.

Improved detection accuracy and  ensuring secure and efficient smart grid operations

This project is a web-based application developed using Python's Flask framework that utilizes Machine Learning to provide personalized medicine, diet, and precaution recommendations based on user-inputted symptoms. The system is designed to act as a preliminary health advisory tool.
This project builds a complete machine learning pipeline to analyze, classify, and predict characteristics of Electric Vehicles (EVs) using a 269k-record real-world EV registration dataset.

MLOptimizer is a comprehensive framework for automatically generating optimized machine learning models while capturing detailed hardware performance metrics. It provides a distributed system for model training, hyperparameter optimization, and hardware resource monitoring.

Today, I explored how to build interactive AI applications using the Gradio framework  a powerful tool that allows you to create simple, shareable web interfaces for your machine learning and Generative AI models.

A multi-level obfuscation framework (mild, moderate, strong) for privacy-preserving machine learning on network-traffic data. Includes dataset balancing, obfuscation scripts, TabNet models, baseline ML benchmarks, and reproducible experiments.

flowMagic is an R package for automated bivariate gating of flow cytometry (FCM) data. It uses a machine-learning model trained on both experts data and a large, high-quality FCM dataset generated by EVE Online players. The package also provides an extensive visualization toolkit and integrates seamlessly with the flowCore/flowWorkspace frameworks
